carry the book out West.

600
01:09:33,915 --> 01:09:37,634
It told me a path had
been laid out for me,

601
01:09:37,635 --> 01:09:41,437
that I'd be led to a
place where the book

602
01:09:41,438 --> 01:09:42,738
would be safe.

603
01:09:46,104 --> 01:09:49,533
Told me that I'd
be protected,

604
01:09:49,534 --> 01:09:52,997
against any one or anything
that stood in my path.

605
01:09:55,976 --> 01:09:58,701
I've been walking ever since.

606
01:10:00,172 --> 01:10:01,315
And you did all that
because a voice

607
01:10:01,316 --> 01:10:03,449
in your head told
you to.

608
01:10:04,262 --> 01:10:05,862
Yes, I did.

609
01:10:06,432 --> 01:10:07,515
I know what I heard.

610
01:10:08,822 --> 01:10:09,878
I know what I hear.

611
01:10:11,139 --> 01:10:12,323
I know I'm not crazy.

612
01:10:13,029 --> 01:10:15,836
And I know I would
have never made it,

613
01:10:15,837 --> 01:10:17,734
without help.

614
01:10:18,217 --> 01:10:21,184
- What's that?
- One question too many.

615
01:10:21,185 --> 01:10:23,705
Go to bed, we've got an
early start in the morning.

616
01:11:26,595 --> 01:11:28,526
What are you doing?

617
01:11:28,527 --> 01:11:30,000
I'm sorry, I thought
you were sleeping.

618
01:11:30,001 --> 01:11:33,662
I wasn't sleeping.
What are you doing?

619
01:11:33,663 --> 01:11:35,191
I just wanted to
see the book.

620
01:11:35,192 --> 01:11:38,794
Nobody touches it but
me, you understand me?

621
01:11:38,795 --> 01:11:41,173
- Do you understand me?
- Yes, I understand.

622
01:11:41,926 --> 01:11:42,748
Go to sleep.

623
01:11:52,877 --> 01:11:54,398
You said you don't know
how to read anyway.

624
01:11:54,399 --> 01:11:56,095
It's of no use to you.

625
01:11:56,096 --> 01:11:57,395
Yeah.

626
01:11:58,376 --> 01:12:00,403
So teach me.

627
01:12:20,035 --> 01:12:22,345
Hold on. Hold up.
Stop!

628
01:12:28,314 --> 01:12:30,050
You say you've been
walking for 30 years, right?

629
01:12:30,251 --> 01:12:31,251
Right.

630
01:12:32,040 --> 01:12:33,817
Have you ever thought
maybe you were lost?

631
01:12:33,818 --> 01:12:35,117
No.

632
01:12:35,118 --> 01:12:37,394
How do you know you're
walking in the right direction?

633
01:12:37,395 --> 01:12:40,012
I walk by faith,
not by sight.

634
01:12:41,067 --> 01:12:43,596
- What does that mean?
- It means you know something,

635
01:12:43,597 --> 01:12:45,933
even if you don't
know something.

636
01:12:45,934 --> 01:12:47,062
It doesn't make
any sense.

637
01:12:47,063 --> 01:12:49,850
It doesn't have to
make sense. It's faith.

638
01:12:49,851 --> 01:12:52,435
Its a flower of light,
in a field of darkness,

639
01:12:52,436 --> 01:12:54,638
giving me the strength
to carry on, understand?

640
01:12:54,639 --> 01:12:56,134
Is that from
your book?

641
01:12:56,135 --> 01:13:00,736
No, it's Johnny Cash.
'Live from Folsom Prison'.

642
01:13:00,737 --> 01:13:02,038
What?

643
01:13:24,420 --> 01:13:26,661
Do you think anyone
lives there?

644
01:13:26,662 --> 01:13:27,962
I don’t know.

645
01:13:29,391 --> 01:13:31,256
Maybe there's water.

646
01:13:41,103 --> 01:13:42,662
Stay behind me.

647
01:13:47,805 --> 01:13:49,792
This is weird.

648
01:14:24,521 --> 01:14:25,716
Who are you?

649
01:14:29,798 --> 01:14:32,545
Travellers, that’s all.
Don't mean any harm.

650
01:14:32,546 --> 01:14:35,861
No trespassing. Didn't
you read the sign?

651
01:14:35,862 --> 01:14:38,311
We're very sorry,
I didn't see it.

652
01:14:39,155 --> 01:14:40,663
- What's your business?
- We were just...

653
01:14:40,664 --> 01:14:42,724
No business.

654
01:14:42,725 --> 01:14:44,858
We're very sorry,
and if you let us,

655
01:14:44,859 --> 01:14:46,729
we'll be on our way.

656
01:14:46,730 --> 01:14:48,638
George, look at them.

657
01:14:48,639 --> 01:14:50,906
One of them is
just a girl.

658
01:14:50,907 --> 01:14:54,203
Old story. Heard it a
hundred times before.

659
01:14:54,204 --> 01:14:56,155
We get so few
visitors these days,

660
01:14:56,156 --> 01:14:58,814
George is suspicious
of everybody.

661
01:14:58,815 --> 01:15:00,649
I'm Martha.

662
01:15:00,650 --> 01:15:02,995
Would you care
for some tea?

663
01:15:13,265 --> 01:15:16,916
How about some music?
It's so soothing.

664
01:15:16,917 --> 01:15:18,218
George!

665
01:15:31,062 --> 01:15:38,055
<I>You can ring my bell,
ring my bell.

666
01:15:38,056 --> 01:15:39,355
How do you like it?

667
01:15:45,931 --> 01:15:52,184
<I>You can ring my bell,
ring my bell.

668
01:15:52,185 --> 01:15:54,951
- Is that good?
- Good, good.

669
01:15:55,552 --> 01:15:56,852
Great.

670
01:16:01,091 --> 01:16:03,039
It's amazing that you
two have survived

671
01:16:03,040 --> 01:16:04,812
out here all by
yourselves.

672
01:16:04,813 --> 01:16:08,592
Well, now. George is
something of a handyman.

673
01:16:10,396 --> 01:16:11,970
He did a lot of
work on this place,

674
01:16:11,971 --> 01:16:13,670
making it safe.

675
01:16:13,671 --> 01:16:16,453
We may be old, but
we're resilient.

676
01:16:17,127 --> 01:16:18,595
We've had more
than a few try to take

677
01:16:18,616 --> 01:16:19,335
this place from us.

678
01:16:19,924 --> 01:16:20,867
Haven't we George?

679
01:16:21,134 --> 01:16:22,860
Yes we have.

680
01:16:23,133 --> 01:16:25,006
I want to show you
something, come on.

681
01:16:25,007 --> 01:16:27,919
George, no. Not now.

682
01:16:28,260 --> 01:16:29,520
Come on!

683
01:16:32,329 --> 01:16:34,851
- Are these...?
- Graves? Sure.

684
01:16:34,852 --> 01:16:37,082
It'd be uncivilized
not to bury them.

685
01:16:37,083 --> 01:16:40,254
Besides, it's good
for the soil.

686
01:16:40,255 --> 01:16:41,899
Come on back inside.

687
01:16:41,900 --> 01:16:44,138
I might be able to rustle
you up some sandwiches.

688
01:16:44,139 --> 01:16:46,295
Well, thank you. Thank
you very much.

689
01:16:46,296 --> 01:16:48,181
- We got to go now.
- They killed all these people.

690
01:16:48,182 --> 01:16:49,592
They didn't just kill
them. They ate them.

691
01:16:49,593 --> 01:16:51,539
- Their hands are shaking.
- Too much human meat.

692
01:16:51,540 --> 01:16:52,840
Let's go.

693
01:16:52,841 --> 01:16:56,042
I found some meat.
I hope you're hungry.

694
01:16:56,043 --> 01:16:57,571
No. No, thank you.

695
01:16:57,572 --> 01:17:01,358
- Well, we got to be going.
- So soon?

696
01:17:01,359 --> 01:17:02,856
Yeah, I'm afraid so.

697
01:17:02,857 --> 01:17:04,236
Are you sure you
won't stay?

