01:35:02,270 --> 01:35:03,618
Get the Engineer!

794
01:36:35,825 --> 01:36:36,902
That's far enough!

795
01:36:38,990 --> 01:36:40,566
What's your
business here?

796
01:36:42,217 --> 01:36:44,709
My name is Eli.

797
01:36:44,908 --> 01:36:47,763
I have a King James
Bible in my possession.

798
01:36:48,032 --> 01:36:50,091
Remain where you are.
Don't attempt to make

799
01:36:50,228 --> 01:36:54,288
any sudden moves, or
you will be fired upon.

800
01:37:10,427 --> 01:37:13,936
Be careful with it.
Thank you.

801
01:37:20,549 --> 01:37:22,526
Careful with it.

802
01:37:32,265 --> 01:37:33,588
Wait.

803
01:37:34,983 --> 01:37:37,983
We've been doing this
for a long time now.

804
01:37:39,954 --> 01:37:40,956
Feels like a museum.

805
01:37:41,016 --> 01:37:43,293
Oh no.
It's much more than that.

806
01:37:43,821 --> 01:37:47,116
This is where we're
going to start again.

807
01:37:47,217 --> 01:37:48,879
We've got a printing
press that will be

808
01:37:48,929 --> 01:37:50,657
operational quite soon.

809
01:37:51,110 --> 01:37:52,433
We're going to teach
people about the

810
01:37:52,473 --> 01:37:53,468
world they lost.

811
01:37:54,702 --> 01:37:56,255
Help them start
to rebuild it.

812
01:37:56,972 --> 01:37:59,507
And look, Shakespeare,
Britannica.

813
01:37:59,537 --> 01:38:01,476
Missing only a
few volumes.

814
01:38:01,667 --> 01:38:03,609
There's a whole series
of beautiful Mozart

815
01:38:03,780 --> 01:38:08,055
and Wagner records. Still
in very pristine condition.

816
01:38:08,056 --> 01:38:11,714
But never a Bible.
Well, not until now.

817
01:38:11,715 --> 01:38:14,380
May I ask what
condition it's in?

818
01:38:16,085 --> 01:38:19,758
It's beat up. But it
will do the job.

819
01:38:21,258 --> 01:38:22,473
Do you think
I could see it?

820
01:38:23,127 --> 01:38:24,363
Yes, you may.

821
01:38:32,075 --> 01:38:34,030
- That's it. It's open.
- Good.

822
01:39:09,070 --> 01:39:10,423
Do you have anything
to write on?

823
01:39:10,424 --> 01:39:14,071
Could you get us some
writing paper, please?

824
01:39:14,072 --> 01:39:15,373
A lot of it.

825
01:39:17,206 --> 01:39:18,908
A whole lot of it.

826
01:39:19,253 --> 01:39:20,552
It can't be.

827
01:39:28,358 --> 01:39:30,309
It's impossible!

828
01:39:31,618 --> 01:39:33,233
It can't be!

829
01:39:36,095 --> 01:39:38,203
Pay close attention.

830
01:39:38,204 --> 01:39:43,641
And write down
everything I say.

831
01:39:44,493 --> 01:39:48,254
Exactly as I say it.

832
01:39:52,308 --> 01:39:58,814
The first book of Moses.
Called Genesis.

833
01:39:59,481 --> 01:40:03,373
Chapter one,
verse one:

834
01:40:06,576 --> 01:40:13,709
"In the beginning God
created the heavens

835
01:40:13,710 --> 01:40:15,111
and the earth. "

836
01:40:19,359 --> 01:40:21,105
Verse two:

837
01:40:22,978 --> 01:40:31,699
"And the earth was
without form and void;

838
01:40:36,172 --> 01:40:43,729
and darkness was upon
the face of the deep.

839
01:40:46,454 --> 01:40:54,954
And the Spirit of God
was hovering

840
01:40:54,955 --> 01:40:58,057
over the face
of the waters. "

841
01:41:01,107 --> 01:41:03,680
Verse three:

842
01:41:06,163 --> 01:41:18,971
"And God said, Let
there be light:

843
01:41:18,972 --> 01:41:21,136
and there was light. "

844
01:41:31,563 --> 01:41:33,890
Where is Solara?

845
01:41:37,004 --> 01:41:41,348
Out there. Her choice.

846
01:41:41,978 --> 01:41:46,889
I tried to bring her
back. She refused.

847
01:41:50,041 --> 01:41:52,825
What did you do
when she refused?

848
01:41:58,635 --> 01:41:59,513
Read it.

849
01:41:59,514 --> 01:42:00,772
What did you do
to my daughter?

850
01:42:00,773 --> 01:42:01,719
Read it!

851
01:42:01,720 --> 01:42:04,850
What did you do
to my daughter!?

852
01:42:23,041 --> 01:42:24,971
You can start anytime.

853
01:42:32,869 --> 01:42:34,170
Sorry.

854
01:42:36,792 --> 01:42:39,920
It's been so long
I don’t remember.

855
01:42:47,030 --> 01:42:50,471
- You have to.
- I have to? Really?

856
01:42:50,472 --> 01:42:52,933
You have to. Please.

857
01:42:56,112 --> 01:43:01,686
- Your leg.
- It doesn't hurt anymore.

858
01:43:02,417 --> 01:43:04,384
I can smell it.

859
01:43:18,996 --> 01:43:21,968
You worked so hard
for that book.

860
01:43:21,969 --> 01:43:26,685
You sacrificed so
much, so many men.

861
01:43:27,948 --> 01:43:30,080
More than you
could spare.

862
01:43:31,934 --> 01:43:34,060
Now, all those people
who were too scared

863
01:43:34,061 --> 01:43:36,989
to even say your name.
They're downstairs,

864
01:43:36,990 --> 01:43:40,262
tearing up the bar right
now, did you know that?

865
01:43:40,841 --> 01:43:43,966
And there's no one
there to stop them.

866
01:43:44,911 --> 01:43:47,553
And you are feverish.

867
01:43:49,691 --> 01:43:51,268
I can't imagine what
it must feel like to

868
01:43:51,269 --> 01:43:53,207
have what you want
so close and it might

869
01:43:53,208 --> 01:43:55,454
as well be a
million miles away.

870
01:43:55,455 --> 01:43:56,758
Stop it!

871
01:44:00,192 --> 01:44:07,102
Are you leaving me?
Claudia?

872
01:44:08,369 --> 01:44:10,355
Claudia!?

873
01:44:13,294 --> 01:44:15,291
Claudia!

874
01:46:03,483 --> 01:46:07,309
Dear Lord. Thank you for
giving me the strength

875
01:46:07,310 --> 01:46:09,098
and the conviction to
complete the task you

876
01:46:09,099 --> 01:46:10,626
entrusted to me.

877
01:46:35,555 --> 01:46:38,670
Thank you for guiding
me straight and true,

878
01:46:38,671 --> 01:46:41,614
through the many
obstacles on my path.

879
01:46:47,237 --> 01:46:49,259
And for keeping me
resolute when all around

880
01:46:49,260 --> 01:46:51,369
seemed lost.

881
01:46:51,721 --> 01:46:53,388
Thank you for your
protection and for your

882
01:46:53,389 --> 01:46:56,190
many signs along
the way.

883
01:46:57,483 --> 01:47:00,201
Thank you for any good
that I may have done,

884
01:47:00,202 --> 01:47:03,445
I'm so sorry
about the bad.

885
01:47:04,083 --> 01:47:05,342
You don't have to
leave, you know.

886
01:47:05,343 --> 01:47:07,561
You're very welcome
to stay here.

887
01:47:07,562 --> 01:47:09,835
You'll be perfectly safe.

888
01:47:09,836 --> 01:47:11,756
Thank you.

889
01:47:11,757 --> 01:47:14,682
But this is something
that I have to do.

890
01:47:19,248 --> 01:47:21,128
Where will you go?

891
01:47:22,229 --> 01:47:23,531
Home.

892
01:47:29,560 --> 01:47:31,826
Thank you for the
friend I made.

893
01:47:31,827 --> 01:47:36,022
Please watch over her,
as you watched over me.

894
01:47:56,391 --> 01:48:00,106
Thank you for finally
allowing me to rest.

895
01:48:00,107 --> 01:48:02,241
I'm so very tired.

896
01:48:02,590 --> 01:48:06,589
But I go now to my
rest at peace.

897
01:48:06,590 --> 01:48:08,506
Knowing that I've done
right with my time

898
01:48:08,507 --> 01:48:10,575
on this earth.

899
01:48:19,262 --> 01:48:25,238
I fought the good fight.
I finished the race.

900
01:48:27,037 --> 01:48:29,857
I kept the faith.

